":true,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.85,"Integration":0.15,"System":0,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":6,"description":"A file that is still being written when the arrival event fires is not picked up for processing until writing is complete","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Real failure: the daemon processes an incomplete file, causing transformation errors or data corruption. Detecting write completion depends on OS and filesystem behavior (file size stability checks, file lock status, or waiting for OS write-completion events). While a Unit test can mock fs.stat returning different sizes over time, this misses OS-level timing issues: on some filesystems, the size might not update immediately; file locks behave differently across Windows/POSIX. A real failure requires either actual file I/O with genuine write timing, or mocking the entire filesystem state machine accurately. System level (with real file writes or precise OS-level event simulation) catches the boundary condition where timing matters.","test_description":"Open a file for writing but leave it partially written. Trigger the file watcher event (via mock or by writing to the filesystem). Verify the daemon detects the file is incompletely written (e.g., by checking file size twice with a delay, checking file locks, or waiting for write-complete OS events). Complete the file write. Verify the daemon then processes the complete file.","plan_consistent":true,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.05,"Integration":0.4,"System":0.55,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}}]},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":10,"cache_creation_input_tokens":13399,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":13399},"output_tokens":4,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"5535ddaa-1793-41ba-a2a4-0c9a4509775c","uuid":"e7c83515-9